So the end of WWII left Korea split between

00:01:15.910 --> 00:01:20.950
a Communist north led by Kim Il crazypants
Sung and an anti-communist but hardly democratic

00:01:20.950 --> 00:01:24.250
South led by Syngman Rhee.
The two were supposed to reunite, but that

00:01:24.250 --> 00:01:29.610
was impossible because they were constantly
fighting that cost around 100,000 lives.

00:01:29.610 --> 00:01:33.400
The civil war between the two Koreas turned
into a full-fledged international conflict

00:01:33.400 --> 00:01:38.810
in June of 1950 when Kim Il Sung invaded the
South, and the US responded. Truman thought

00:01:38.810 --> 00:01:42.250
that Kim’s invasion was being pushed by
the Soviets and that it was a challenge to

00:01:42.250 --> 00:01:45.420
the “Free World.”
Truman went to the United Nations and he got

00:01:45.420 --> 00:01:50.210
authorization, but he didn’t go to Congress
and never called the Korean War a “war.”

00:01:50.210 --> 00:01:54.750
Insisting instead that American troops were
leading a UN “police action” but that

00:01:54.750 --> 00:01:58.060
was kind of a misleading statement.
General Douglas MacArthur was in command of

00:01:58.060 --> 00:02:01.660
this tiny little police force at the start
of the war because he was the highest ranking

00:02:01.660 --> 00:02:05.810
general in the region. He was also really
popular, at least with the press, although

00:02:05.810 --> 00:02:08.780
not so much with other generals, or with the
president.

00:02:08.780 --> 00:02:12.890
Under MacArthur, UN forces – which basically
meant American and South Korean forces -- pushed

00:02:12.890 --> 00:02:17.770
the North Koreans back past the 38th parallel
where the two countries had been divided,

00:02:17.770 --> 00:02:22.940
and then Truman made a fateful decision: The
United States would try to re-unify Korea

00:02:22.940 --> 00:02:26.140
as a non-communist state.
Which, if you’ve looked at a map recently,

00:02:26.140 --> 00:02:30.590
you’ll notice went swimmingly. America’s
allies and the UN all agreed to this idea,

00:02:30.590 --> 00:02:35.590
so up north they went, all the way to the
northern border with China at the Yalu river.

00:02:35.590 --> 00:02:39.480
At that point, Chinese forces, feeling that
American forces were a smidge too close to

00:02:39.480 --> 00:02:44.430
China, counter-attacked on November 1, 1950
and by Christmas the two sides were stalemated

00:02:44.430 --> 00:02:47.780
again at the 38th parallel, right where they
started.

00:02:47.780 --> 00:02:51.819
The war dragged on for two more years with
the U.S. pursuing a “scorched earth” policy

00:02:51.819 --> 00:02:56.210
and dropping more bombs on Korea than had
been dropped in the entire Pacific theater

00:02:56.210 --> 00:02:59.240
during WWII.
The two sides tried to negotiate a peace treaty,

00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:03.010
but the sticking point was the repatriation
of North Korean and Chinese prisoners who

00:03:03.010 --> 00:03:05.270
didn’t want to go back to their communist
homelands.

00:03:05.270 --> 00:03:09.010
Meanwhile, at home, Americans were growing
tired of a war that they weren’t winning,

00:03:09.010 --> 00:03:12.150
which helped to swing the election of 1952
for Dwight Eisenhower.

00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:16.200
Also he was also running against perennial
presidential loser Adlai Stevenson, who was

00:03:16.200 --> 00:03:19.740
perceived as an egghead intellectual because
his name was Adlai Stevenson.

00:03:19.740 --> 00:03:24.100
In addition to helping get Ike elected, the
Korean War had a number of profound effects.

00:03:24.100 --> 00:03:29.150
First and most importantly, it was expensive,
both in terms of lives and money.

00:03:29.150 --> 00:03:35.740
In 3 years of fighting 33,629 Americans were
killed, 102,000 were wounded and nearly 4

00:03:35.740 --> 00:03:41.440
million Koreans and Chinese were killed, wounded,
or missing. The majority of Korean casualties

00:03:41.440 --> 00:03:44.630
were civilians.
The Korean War also further strengthened executive

00:03:44.630 --> 00:03:48.709
power in the United States – Truman went
to war without a declaration and Congress

00:03:48.709 --> 00:03:52.550
acquiesced – this doesn’t mean that the
war was initially was unpopular, it wasn’t.

00:03:52.550 --> 00:03:56.560
People wanted to see America do something
about Communism and allowing Kim to take the

00:03:56.560 --> 00:04:00.550
south and possibly threaten Japan was unacceptable.
However, the whole idea that you don’t really

00:04:00.550 --> 00:04:05.680
need to declare war to go to war, while not
new in America, sure has been important the

00:04:05.680 --> 00:04:07.599
last 60 years.
And the Korean War also strengthened the Cold

00:04:07.599 --> 00:04:10.900
War mentality. I mean, this was the height
of the Red Scare.

